configDescription.message:
Reprint can automatically extract the body of a web page and publish it to any place you allow.
In addition to the settings here, you should also configure the server-side publishing interface, see: Common software publishing Plug-in and custom publishing interface docking document

syncDescription.message:
Please note: You need to log in in the Chrome browser on all devices (including this device) so that the sync options can be used normally.
You can view this page on other devices to check whether the synchronization takes effect.

releaseDescription.message:
You should provide an interface for users to accept the Reprint request and perform the save operation.
See: Commonly used software publishing plug-ins or custom publishing interface docking documents

releasePlaceholder.message: Please enter the publishing address, such as: https://itdashu.com..

releaseTip.message: In order to prevent abuse, the newly added configuration must be checked and saved after passing the test. Issue interface verification instructions

historyDescription.message:
Records that failed to publish in use will appear here.
There are only 20 records kept here, and when you click on an entry in the release list, the entry will be deleted from the list.

releaseUrlResponseError.message: The interface response is illegal, the interface needs to return a json object, and contains the code and msg fields

releaseUrlTestError.message: Request to publish the interface failed. Please check the network or the interface server is abnormal
